Letters to a Busy World

By Nicholas Lawson

Preface


This is 3 months of letters I wrote out to various members of the national east coast community and Ohio and I find it cathartic to sit and write a letter and I am saving them here which is a unique posture because in hand written letter days once you sent a letter off you didn’t havea copy of it. This is a cross section of the programming I did that is in line with Donald Trump’s push for peace on earth. I am participating in peace on earth and find that Donald Trump is doing a great job. He has peace on his mind and it’s bringing him peace of mind.

I envision a world where it’s the information super highway where letters pop and pop out at fast rates and it’s our speed of communication and processing of communication that dictates how far in the future we are. I think that as we process information faster and faster and send more information and more people process more information we can state we are in the future the more producers we have the more future we belong to.

