Letter to English Department

Dear Lora L Anderson,

I have been exploring automatic publishing now for 15 years since I graduated from the University of Cincinnati with an English Literature Degree after having spent 10 years studying because I had trouble in school that needed Disabilities assistance.

I have these books https://www.amazon.com/author/nicholaslawsonhealthy I am exploring immediate publishing with Amazon and I use them as a product on https://slushpile.github.io which took me 4 years to put together just recently and I have https://www.vitaemagazineblog.wordpress.com and I’m fleshed out. All my publishable works are published. I don’t even think in terms of a literary agent right now. I think in terms of self promotion to universities ala the internet.

This internet hasn’t even been discovered yet. The authors don’t know coding and the coders don’t know authoring and here I sit with almost a digital design degree from DAAP and I find myself interested in opinions now mostly. I sought out my alma mater at Uc and your professional accolades seemed like the perfect person to ask.

What do you think of my work? I have about 300k tweets dating back to 2012 and I am constantly writing and sharing links. I have freedom to work online and I don’t take that freedom lightly. I did something academic to the internet and I think I did a good job.

 What do I need from you? An opinion. The number one feature I find of writing online on Facebook and Twitter for the most part, even if you’re writing for a local television station or radio station, is that you work in silence. No one ever responds. That’s the main feature of the internet I find is the wallishness of it.

So since that’s true I’ll wrap up here but a local graduate is now free from weed and just a little more professional than on weed and it’s regular writing from now on. My family moved up to Lebanon Ohio after a violence streak in NCH just near my folks house involving guns and we all packed up and took off. North College Hill used to be so nice we had a pool and tennis court and basketball court and 3 pizza shops and a candy store and a baseball card store and a skate shop and a bakery that made donuts. It was so nice. I don’t know what happened I was busy in school.

I’m nick lawson i’m a writer with excellent typing skills.

I was saying hello.

I think my problem with the university in the past was my weed habit that have now put down. Sobriety from weed is better than weed.

sincerely,

Nicholas Lawson

